**Dashboard Gradient Hierarchy:**
1. Lightest (cards): #F0F7FD → #E0EDFB
2. Medium (containers): #E0EDFB → #C7DDEF  
3. Dark (icon accents): #5B93D7 → #2E5AAC
4. Darkest (headers): #5B93D7 → #2E5AAC → #1C3667

**Color Usage Guidelines:**
- **Blue**: Primary brand color for most UI elements (buttons, headers, links, primary actions)
- **Gold**: Accent color for premium features, achievements, highlights, special designations
- **Blue-Gold Combination**: Executive dashboards, premium features, high-value clients, partner-level views
- Use gold sparingly to maintain impact and visual hierarchy

## Component Usage

Use UI components from `/src/components/ui/` - all variants, props, and styling are handled internally:

```typescript
// Buttons - primary, secondary, gradient, danger
<Button variant="gradient" size="lg" icon={icon} loading={isLoading}>Create</Button>

// Cards - standard, dashboard, shared-service, stats
<Card variant="dashboard" hoverable loading={isLoading}>
  <div className="p-4">Content</div>
</Card>

// Dashboard Cards - interactive with hover, stats, icons
<DashboardCard 
  title="Tax Services" 
  icon={icon} 
  href="/path"
  stats={[{ label: 'Active', value: 42, primary: true }]}
/>

// Inputs - text, email, password, textarea, select
<Input variant="text" label="Email" error="Invalid" />

// Banners - info, error, warning, success
<Banner variant="error" title="Error" message="Message" dismissible />

// Stats - gradient cards with 4 hierarchy variants
<StatCard label="Active" value={42} icon={icon} gradientVariant={1} />

// Loading
<LoadingSpinner size="md" color="blue" />
<LoadingOverlay message="Loading..." />

// Badges
<Badge variant="green" dot>Active</Badge>
```

**Icon Sizing:** h-4 w-4 (small), h-5 w-5 (regular), h-6 w-6 (large)

